# ThreatForge Output — SIGNATURES
# CVE:       CVE-2026-54528
# Product:   jupyterlab
# Tags:      [HIGH]
# Score:     20
# Tier:      MONITOR
# Generated: 2026-07-14T21:07:46.066281Z
# Status:    OK
# ---

# Confidence: No public PoC known — pattern inferred from the
# CVE/advisory description only.
# No packet-capture (PCAP) data source is available to this pipeline —
# this pattern is NOT verified against captured exploit traffic.
#
# Vulnerability summary: CVE-2026-54528 — JupyterLab Git < 0.54.0
# information disclosure via case-insensitive bypass of excluded_paths
# in GitHandler.prepare() using fnmatch.fnmatchcase(). Authenticated
# users on case-insensitive filesystems may read directories that
# should be excluded. Fix shipped in v0.54.0 [3].
#
# Detection rationale: The JupyterLab Git extension exposes a REST API
# at /git/<repo>/... path space. An attacker exploiting this flaw would
# issue HTTP requests to git API endpoints using mixed/upper-case path
# segments to bypass fnmatch.fnmatchcase() exclusion checks. This rule
# looks for HTTP requests to the jupyterlab-git REST handler where the
# URI path contains uppercase or mixed-case variants of "git" that
# could defeat case-sensitive fnmatch exclusion logic. The pcre pattern
# targets path components that include at least one uppercase letter in
# the "git" API prefix, which would be the mechanism of bypass on
# case-insensitive filesystems.
#
# Limitations: Without PCAP or PoC data, the exact HTTP path structure
# used to bypass fnmatch.fnmatchcase() is not confirmed. Analysts should
# validate this pattern against actual JupyterLab Git traffic before
# enabling in blocking mode. False positive risk is moderate in
# environments where JupyterLab is widely deployed.
#
# IMPORTANT — DRAFT FOR ANALYST REVIEW ONLY. Validate before deployment.

alert http $EXTERNAL_NET any -> $HOME_NET any (
  msg:"THREATFORGE CVE-2026-54528 JupyterLab Git excluded_paths case-insensitive bypass attempt";
  flow:established,to_server;
  http.uri;
  content:"/git/";
  pcre:"/\/[Gg][Ii][Tt]\/(?:[A-Z][^\/]*\/|[^\/]*[A-Z][^\/]*\/)/U";
  http.header;
  content:"Authorization";
  reference:cve,2026-54528;
  metadata:mitre_technique_id T1083, is_kev false, status experimental;
  classtype:policy-violation;
  sid:9000042; rev:1; )

